<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>an ant
<br>
carries more than its weight&nbsp;&#8212;
<br>
morning prayer
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Ted van Zutphen
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM3></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>summer opera&nbsp;&#8212;
<br>
her fan stops fluttering
<br>
during the main aria
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Tomislav Maretic
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM5></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>creak of floorboards
<br>
the musty shop smell
<br>
of ancient hardwoods
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
James Chessing
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM7></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>the drought year
<br>
written in flies
<br>
on the river-bed
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Michael McClintock
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM9></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>cliff dwellings
<br>
my perspiration salts
<br>
ancient stone
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Tom Painting
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
